@NODE "Whatisit" "What is it ?"

What is TicTacFoozle ?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Description
~~~~~~~~~~~
TicTacFoozle is the computerised version of noughts and crosses making
it much easier to play with other people via local echoes or netmail.
It also erradicates the need to removed multiple quote arrows. When playing
by netmail a certain amount of tweaking will be needed to change the
address and you should not play in an area which contains no mail as your
first message will have no name in the from field - who knows why!

FEATURES
~~~~~~~~
o New games started easily
o Saves you removing multiple quoting arrows
o Easy to make moves
o Large display
o Nice fonts & GUI interface
o Written partly by Creepy ;)
o Nice Guide file and installer script!
@ENDNODE

@NODE InstallationUsage "Installation & Usage"
  How do I install it then, is this going to be very hard or like a banana
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                             soft and yellow ?
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


INSTALLING AFM
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Unpack the fonts and place in fonts: if you have any librries around then
place these in libs:, place brun in c: and makemail must be in mail:bin.
Then edit the script and you are off! Next shove the file into your rexx:
directory and call it from the external menu (foozle.ext) using

"TicTacFooz" rx rexx:tictacfooz %d %n %F %s


USING TTF
~~~~~~~~~

To use TTF you simply select the menu option like any other (providing you
have chosen to install the script as instructed above.). You will then be
asked if you want to Scan or Start - if you have a message with a game in
click on scan - if not then click on start, and answer the questions.
Unlike previous version you will not have to select which piece (X or O)
you are using more than once. When you have followed either of these
instructions you will be presented with a grid and some options. Select
where you want to place the piece by using the Top,Middle or Bottom
selectors and the Left,Right and Middle keys. If you try and place a piece
where there is already one then the proggy will exit - USE the grid ;) This
should be used from Netmail or local echoes only as you may receive
messages from unhappy moderators otherwise and may ultimately asked to
enter a read-only state on specific echoes if your behaviour persists. this
is because some people don't like noughts and crosses as they feel they are
far above it.  If this is the case, smile to yourself and have another game
of TTF via netmail. This will mean changing the address field every time
you play (I haven't implemented Netmail playing for Foozle yet) but it is
not too much hassle.


@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"
                          History and Future Development
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
v1.0

By Paul, pretty good - but for Spot only, so I rewrote and added some
features - and a lovely GUI ;) and got

v2.0 - the present version which I will release for Spot at the same time.
I may also do a conversion to MM if I have the time!

v2.1 - added new fonts and have also added a new bigger grid for those who
want to plan things on a big scale!

Future:

I may add a bigger playing field and change the object to one like a game
called ooze - wherby you have to cover the majority of the board - but
that could take ages to work out - so we'll see! I'll add netmail support
for v2.1 and a config file generator in the install script
@ENDNODE

